parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mechanical failure can cause the vehicle to lose compression, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle starts to smoke
loses compression
and may experience a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition wiring failure can cause the vehicle to lose all electrical power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle loses all electrical power while in motion
may not start
or loses power when put into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shift failure can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly shift into gear, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts out of park and into reverse without warning
potentially causing accidents or damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a fire, potentially leading to damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, as well as posing a risk to the safety of the occupants.
symptoms: Smoke emanates from the ignition switch
the ignition switch starts smoking
a burning smell is present
the ignition switch fails to function properly
a cable next to the brake booster melts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, causing drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, which can result in accidents, especially on highways or in remote areas.
symptoms: The fuel gauge needle fluctuates or sticks
the fuel gauge does not move
the fuel gauge reads inaccurately
the fuel gauge does not respond to changes in fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive fuel leakage from the fuel tank can cause fires, explosions, or environmental hazards, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants, other road users, and the environment.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor inside or outside the vehicle
visible fuel leaks
fuel puddles under the vehicle
decreased fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sagging or hanging headliner fabric can obstruct the rearview, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headliner fabric is hanging down
obstructing the rearview
the headliner fabric is sagging

the headliner fabric is loose and obstructing vision.
